verses.text: At that time the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto me, Hew thee two tables of stone like unto the first , and come up unto me into the mount , and make thee an ark of wood.
And I will write on the tables the words that were in the first tables which thou brakest , and thou shalt put them in the ark.
And I made an ark \add of\add* shittim wood , and hewed two tables of stone like unto the first , and went up into the mount , having the two tables in mine hand.

And he wrote on the tables , according to the first writing , the ten commandments , which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* spake unto you in the mount out of the midst of the fire in the day of the assembly : and the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* gave them unto me.  +  r 10.4  t commandments: Heb. words *
And I turned myself and came down from the mount , and put the tables in the ark which I had made ; and there they be, as the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* commanded me. \p

¶ And the children of Israel took their journey from Beeroth of the children of Jaakan to Mosera : there Aaron died , and there he was buried ; and Eleazar his son ministered in the priest’s office in his stead.
From thence they journeyed unto Gudgodah ; and from Gudgodah to Jotbath , a land of rivers of waters. \p

¶ At that time the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* separated the tribe of Levi , to bear the ark of the covenant of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, to stand before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* to minister unto him, and to bless in his name , unto this day.

Wherefore Levi hath no part nor inheritance with his brethren ; the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* his inheritance , according as the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God promised him.

And I stayed in the mount , according to the first time , forty days and forty nights ; and the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* hearkened unto me at that time also, \add and\add* the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* would not destroy thee.  +  r 10.10  t first…: or, former days *

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto me, Arise , take \add thy\add* journey before the people , that they may go in and possess the land , which I sware unto their fathers to give unto them.\f + \fr 10.11 \ft take…: Heb. go in journey\f* \p

¶ And now, Israel , what doth the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God require of thee, but to fear the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God , to walk in all his ways , and to love him, and to serve the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God with all thy heart and with all thy soul ,
To keep the commandments of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and his statutes , which I command thee this day for thy good ?
Behold, the heaven and the heaven of heavens \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God , the earth \add also\add*, with all that therein \add is\add*.
Only the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had a delight in thy fathers to love them, and he chose their seed after them, \add even\add* you above all people , as \add it is\add* this day.
Circumcise therefore the foreskin of your heart , and be no more stiffnecked.
For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God \add is\add* God of gods , and Lord of lords , a great God , a mighty , and a terrible , which regardeth not persons , nor taketh reward :
He doth execute the judgment of the fatherless and widow , and loveth the stranger , in giving him food and raiment.
Love ye therefore the stranger : for ye were strangers in the land of Egypt.
Thou shalt fear the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God ; him shalt thou serve , and to him shalt thou cleave , and swear by his name.
He \add is\add* thy praise , and he \add is\add* thy God , that hath done for thee these great and terrible things , which thine eyes have seen.
Thy fathers went down into Egypt with threescore and ten persons ; and now the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God hath made thee as the stars of heaven for multitude.
